"title": "5582: tiredness",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5582: tiredness",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>A natural outcome of work and stress for which God has provided relief, rest and renewal.  Scripture recognises that tiredness may have spiritual, as well as physical, causes.</p>\n<h2>Causes of tiredness</h2>\n<h3>Work</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt8:24\">MAT 8:24</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark4:38\">MRK 4:38</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:23\">LUK 8:23</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl10:15\">ECC 10:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl12:12\">ECC 12:12</a></p>\n<h3>Afflictions and stress</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job16:7\">JOB 16:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam17:29\">2SA 17:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs19:3-1Kgs19:5\">1KI 19:3–19:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps69:3\">PSA 69:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor12:15\">2CO 12:15</a></p>\n<h3>Concern and anxiety</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps31:9-Ps31:10\">PSA 31:9–31:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps6:6\">PSA 6:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps32:3-Ps32:4\">PSA 32:3–32:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps119:28\">PSA 119:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer45:3\">JER 45:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:45\">LUK 22:45</a></p>\n<h3>Desire for money and possessions</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov23:4\">PRO 23:4</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Travelling</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut25:18\">DEU 25:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg8:4\">JDG 8:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam16:14\">2SA 16:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John4:6\">JHN 4:6</a></p>\n<h3>Old age</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl12:3\">ECC 12:3</a></p>\n<h3>Zeal for the Lord's work</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps119:139\">PSA 119:139</a></p>\n<h3>Battles</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg4:21\">JDG 4:21</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam14:31\">1SA 14:31</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam21:15\">2SA 21:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam23:10\">2SA 23:10</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer51:30\">JER 51:30</a></p>\n<h3>Sin and rebellion</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa57:10\">ISA 57:10</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer9:5\">JER 9:5</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek23:43\">EZK 23:43</a></p>\n<h3>Foolishness</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl1:8\">ECC 1:8</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa46:1\">ISA 46:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa47:13\">ISA 47:13</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer12:13\">JER 12:13</a></p>\n<h2>Help from God to deal with tiredness</h2>\n<h3>God's promises of help and rest</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa40:28-Isa40:31\">ISA 40:28–40:31</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa46:4\">ISA 46:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor9:8\">2CO 9:8</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ offers rest and encouragement</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt11:28-Matt11:30\">MAT 11:28–11:30</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev2:2-Rev2:3\">REV 2:2–2:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark6:31\">MRK 6:31</a></p>\n<h3>Trusting God as the antidote to anxiety and sorrow</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt6:25-Matt6:27\">MAT 6:25–6:27</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:25-Luke12:27\">LUK 12:25–12:27</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps119:28\">PSA 119:28</a></p>\n<h3>God's provision of times for rest</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen1:5\">GEN 1:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen2:2\">GEN 2:2</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod20:8-Exod20:11\">EXO 20:8–20:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut5:12-Deut5:15\">DEU 5:12–5:15</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps127:2\">PSA 127:2</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer31:25\">JER 31:25</a></p>\n<h2>Help from others to deal with tiredness</h2>\n<h3>Encouragements to be strong in the Lord and to persevere</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps27:14\">PSA 27:14</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor15:58\">1CO 15:58</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal6:9\">GAL 6:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Thess3:13\">2TH 3:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb12:1-Heb12:3\">HEB 12:1–12:3</a></p>\n<h3>God's help channelled through others</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa50:4\">ISA 50:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor1:3-2Cor1:4\">2CO 1:3–1:4</a></p>\n<h3>Physical help from others</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam16:2\">2SA 16:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod17:12\">EXO 17:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg8:15\">JDG 8:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam17:28-2Sam17:29\">2SA 17:28–17:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs19:5-1Kgs19:6\">1KI 19:5–19:6</a></p>\n<h3>Advice about lifestyle</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod18:17-Exod18:23\">EXO 18:17–18:23</a></strong></p>",
